 The President Muhammadu Buhari regime has deployed heavily-armed security operatives to disrupt a protest demanding the release of human rights activist, Omoyele Sowore in Abuja. The security agents surrounded the Unity Fountain in Abuja, venue of the planned protest alongside a group of pro-government demonstrators. The protest is targeted at pressuring the Nigerian government to release political prisoners like Sowore, social media influencer, Dadiyata, as well as Stephen Kefas.